ToTimeLong
public string ToTimeLong()

Returns full time with milliseconds (HH:MM:SS:MMMM)

Example
var time = new ClockTime { Hours = 14, Minutes = 30, Seconds = 45, Milliseconds = 500 };
string result = time.ToTimeLong(); // "14:30:45:0500"
Returns

Formatted time string with milliseconds

ToTimeShort
public string ToTimeShort()

Returns short time format (HH:MM:SS)

Example
var time = new ClockTime { Hours = 9, Minutes = 5, Seconds = 30 };
string result = time.ToTimeShort(); // "09:05:30"
Returns

Formatted time string without milliseconds

ToTimeAMPM
public string ToTimeAMPM()

Returns time in 12-hour format with AM/PM

Example
var time = new ClockTime { Hours = 23, Minutes = 15, Seconds = 0 };
string result = time.ToTimeAMPM(); // "11:15:00 PM"
Returns

Formatted 12-hour time string with period marker

ToTimeFull
public string ToTimeFull()

Returns combined full date and time

Example
var time = new ClockTime { Days = 25, Months = 12, Years = 2023, Hours = 18, Minutes = 0, Seconds = 30, Milliseconds = 250 };
string result = time.ToTimeFull(); // "25/12/2023 - 18:00:30:0250"
Returns

Combined date and time string

ToYears
public string ToYears()

Converts total time to years

Example
var time = new ClockTime { TotalTime = 63072000000 }; // 2 years
string result = time.ToYears(); // "2"
Returns

Total duration in years
